:1_2-66"><sup><i><b>bo</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-:1_2-67"><sup><i><b>bp</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-:1_2-68"><sup><i><b>bq</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-:1_2-69"><sup><i><b>br</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-:1_2-70"><sup><i><b>bs</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-:1_2-71"><sup><i><b>bt</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-:1_2-72"><sup><i><b>bu</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-:1_2-73"><sup><i><b>bv</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFEly1995" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/James_W._Ely_Jr." title="James W. Ely Jr.">Ely, James W.</a> (1995). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=NDcMCAAAQBAJ"><i>The Chief Justiceship of Melville W. Fuller, 1888–1910</i></a>. Columbia, SC: <a href="/wiki/University_of_South_Carolina_Press" title="University of South Carolina Press">University of South Carolina Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1-57003-018-5" title="Special:BookSources/978-1-57003-018-5"><bdi>978-1-57003-018-5</bdi></a>. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20181130183805/https://books.google.com/books?id=NDcMCAAAQBAJ">Archived</a> from the original on November 30, 2018<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">March 3,</span> 2021</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Chief+Justiceship+of+Melville+W.+Fuller%2C+1888%E2%80%931910&amp;rft.place=Columbia%2C+SC&amp;rft.pub=University+of+South+Carolina+Press&amp;rft.date=1995&amp;rft.isbn=978-1-57003-018-5&amp;rft.aulast=Ely&amp;rft.aufirst=James+W.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DNDcMCAAAQBAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMelville+Fuller" class="Z3988"></span></span>
